  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6485.88 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6475 (-13.1B) and positive gamma at 6490 (+1.0B), dealers are caught in a whipsaw zone where they're forced to buy any dip toward 6475 and sell any rally above 6490, creating violent two-way action. The breakout regime with -8.5B total GEX means dealers will amplify whatever directional move develops, so expect explosive momentum once we clear either the 6475 buy wall or 6490 sell wall decisively. Watch for a break below 6475 to trigger aggressive dealer buying that could spark a sharp reversal, while a sustained move above 6490 should see dealer selling pressure increase as we approach the 6500-6515 negative gamma cluster.",
